Second i wanna tell you, I‚Äôm not good at dating. I‚Äôm not good at ‚Äúlet‚Äôs be casual,‚Äù or ‚Äúwe‚Äôll see where this goes.‚Äù
See, that‚Äôs the thing‚ÄîI want to know where this is going. I want to know the purpose ‚Äî because why have something meaningless? Life‚Äôs too damn short for meaningless.
No, I‚Äôm not crazy. I don‚Äôt need to know your favorite color, your deepest fear, and if you think you‚Äôll fall in love with me on our very first date. But I‚Äôd like to. I‚Äôd like to know the way your mind works, if it‚Äôs calm and patient, nervous and hesitant, or if you‚Äôre just as passionate as me.
I want to know everything about you. The real you, and I want to fall into you, unafraid. I want us to go somewhere, not sit stagnant and still. Love isn‚Äôt stagnant and still.
And I‚Äôm not the ‚Äòwe‚Äôre just messing around‚Äô type of girl. I don‚Äôt ‚Äòmess around.‚Äô Why give you pieces of myself when you can‚Äôt even commit to staying? I won‚Äôt be able to make you fall in love with me, and frankly, I shouldn‚Äôt have to try. So no, I won‚Äôt ‚Äòmess around‚Äô because at the end of the day, we‚Äôre just wasting each other‚Äôs time. We‚Äôre just keeping one another from falling in love.
And no matter how we try to convince ourselves otherwise, that‚Äôs what we‚Äôre all searching for.
If I‚Äôm being honest, I don‚Äôt understand the dating world. I don‚Äôt understand the quickness, the half-heartedness, the jumping from person to person and the ‚Äòfeeling things out‚Äô. When I spend time with someone, when I start to get to understand them, when I let them see me in all that I am, that‚Äôs everything to me. and i'll treat you more then i loved my self. 
I don‚Äôt know how to shut off the stream of emotions, the excited butterflies when I hear their name, the passion I feel for wanting to discover who they are behind their surface.
I can‚Äôt help wanting to fall for them. Not nervously, not hesitantly, and sure as hell not casually. Is that so wrong?

First i wanna tell, This is what putting in effort actually means.
Putting in effort is not texting you when it‚Äôs convenient. It‚Äôs not answering your messages, as long as you‚Äôre the one that texts first. It‚Äôs not agreeing to hang out with you, but only if you‚Äôre the one that makes the plans and finds a time that works for you both.
Effort is texting you during their lunch break, even though they only have a few minutes to spare. It‚Äôs asking you if you‚Äôre free days in advance so that you don‚Äôt miss out on a moment together.
Effort is showing up at your house with pizza, even though you didn‚Äôt ask them to order one. It‚Äôs trying their hardest to make you smile, so that you don‚Äôt feel like the love is one-sided.
Sending a good morning text isn‚Äôt enough ‚Äî not if that‚Äôs the only thing that they are doing. You shouldn‚Äôt be happy to wake up to a text that claims they care about you when they never prove it. You shouldn‚Äôt be happy to hear that they miss you if they don‚Äôt actually do anything about it.
Words aren‚Äôt enough. They should be taking action. They should be doing whatever they can to see you. Because effort is more than making promises. It‚Äôs keeping promises.
If they care about you, they aren‚Äôt going to let life get in the way. It doesn‚Äôt matter how busy they are. They can make time for the things that matter.¬†
If they want you enough, then they will either find time or make time.
But if they don‚Äôt want you enough, if they are only semi-serious about you, then they will put in minimal effort to try to keep you around. They will continue saying that they miss you. They will say that they want to hang out ‚Äî but will never set a date.
They will apologize for being so neglectful and promise that things are going to be different soon. They will string you along for as long as they can.
That‚Äôs why you need to walk away. Walk away, because being there for you half the time isn‚Äôt enough. Walk away, because things are never going to change if you keep letting this slide.
You shouldn‚Äôt be stuck doing all of the work in a relationship. You deserve someone who wants to show up for you.

This is for the friends I will grow old with. The people who have been there from the beginning, and the people who have proven that they will be there until the end.

Thank you for always being there when I needed you. For being selfless and listening to everything I had to get off of my chest, for picking me up when I felt like I couldn‚Äôt possibly do so myself.

Thank you for always being truthful with me. For being the type of person who had the ability to tell me I was wrong, who respected me enough to challenge me to be better, do better, and think better. Thank you for always being understanding, for always allowing for me to express myself and to feel what I was feeling, but thank you for loving me enough to tell me when I was overreacting ‚Äî thank you for loving me enough to demand I get out of my own head.

Thank you for bringing joy to my life. For making me laugh so hard I‚Äôve had coffee come out of my nostrils, for all of our inside jokes and all of those monumental mistakes we look back on and smile about. And thank you for the other kind of joy you have brought to my life ‚Äî the kind of joy that comes from knowing you are understood; from knowing that there is someone else in the world who gets you on a level most people don‚Äôt.¬†
Thank you for simply being you. You inspire me to be a softer person, you motivate me to do more and see more and feel more, because you‚Äôre always right there encouraging me to do so. They say the best kind of friend is the one who is always cheering you on, the one who is always showing you your potential, and that is exactly what you do. You are such a positive force in my life, and I feel as if there aren‚Äôt enough words in the English language to explain just how much you mean to me.

Thank you for choosing me. You aren‚Äôt just a friend to me, you‚Äôre a soul friend ‚Äî the type of person who changes someone‚Äôs life, who makes everything that much better.

When it comes to friendships, you need the kind of people in your life who love you for you.
You need the kind of people who you can talk about the complicated parts of your life with. The kind of people who won‚Äôt judge you, the kind of people who will listen to you and hold you when you‚Äôre crying because you can‚Äôt make sense of what‚Äôs going on. The kind of people you can rely on, no matter how near or far they are from you.
You need the kind of people who inspire you to do better. The kind of people who balance you out but always support your dreams. The kind of people who make you want to be a better person and feel like you‚Äôre able to do anything with their support.
Everyone needs someone to lean on in life when things get complicated and the world feels dark. You need someone to talk you off the ledge you‚Äôre on, someone to reassure you everything is going to be okay when you feel like the world is crumbling down on you, someone to believe in you when you don‚Äôt believe in yourself.
It‚Äôs easy to feel alone in the world, to feel misunderstood and used. But, you have to find the people who make you feel less alone, the people who actually might not understand what you‚Äôre going through but try their best to put themselves in your shoes and see what you‚Äôre seeing.¬†
You need the kind of people who have your best interest at heart because those are the kind of people who are worth fighting for, those are the kind of people we all need in our lives. The kind of people you can count on when everything goes dark, when your heart breaks and you feel like you‚Äôve hit rock bottom. Those are the people who matter, not the ones who are only there when things are good, not the ones who are only there when things are convenient for them.

caption.text: Depression is the result of over thinking. The mind creates problems that didn't even exist...

Jangan berpikir kalau bersedih artinya kamu lemah atau kalah. Sedih jugalah perasaan, ini adalah yang normal. Setiap orang pasti merasakanya. Biarkanlah dirimu merasakan apa yang harus kamu rasakan itu. Tak apa kita jatuh, tak apa kita salah. Dan tidak apa jika kita sedih hari ini dan ingin menangis, sungguh tidak apa. 
Terimalah perasaan sedih dan galau ini saat mereka datang, tapi ketahuilah kalau mereka hanya pengunjung sementara, mereka tidak akan tinggal selamanya. Ketahuilah kalau kamu punya kekuatan untuk menentukan nasibmu sendiri. Kamu bisa dilanda kesedihan, tapi kamu tetap bisa memilih untuk terus berjuang.
